# To create a new migration:

```
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<migration_message>"
```

# To apply migrations:

```
alembic upgrade head
```

# To revert the last migration:

```
alembic downgrade -1
```

# To view current revision:

```
alembic current
```

# To view the history of migrations:

```
alembic history
```

# To view the SQL that would be run for an upgrade:

```
alembic upgrade head --sql
```

# To view the SQL that would be run for a downgrade:

```
alembic downgrade -1 --sql
```

# To stamp the database with a specific revision without running migrations:

```
alembic stamp head
```
